The paper discusses the use of Markov logic networks (MLNs) for finding the most probable and coherent ontology from a knowledge base, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces a novel way to deal with concrete domains, which is relevant to databases (cs.DB) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the algorithm, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE).
